- keep the package-acceptance workflow assertion aligned with full-release-validation concurrency
- keep plugin prerelease test-plan assertions aligned with openclaw-release-checks concurrency

## Real behavior proof
Behavior addressed: release workflow assertions now match the actual alpha cancellation contract shipped in the workflow YAML.
Real environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout on Linux, Node v22.22.2, pnpm 11.1.0, with dependencies installed by `pnpm install`.
Exact steps or command run after this patch: parsed the real workflow YAML with `node` and `yaml`, then ran the focused workflow assertion tests, oxfmt check, and diff whitespace check.
Evidence after fix: terminal output from the real checkout:
```text
$ node --input-type=module <<'NODE'
import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';
import { parse } from 'yaml';
for (const file of ['.github/workflows/openclaw-release-checks.yml', '.github/workflows/full-release-validation.yml']) {
  const workflow = parse(readFileSync(file, 'utf8'));
  console.log(file);
  console.log(`  group: ${workflow.concurrency.group}`);
  console.log(`  cancel-in-progress: ${workflow.concurrency['cancel-in-progress']}`);
}
NODE
.github/workflows/openclaw-release-checks.yml
  group: openclaw-release-checks-${{ inputs.expected_sha || inputs.ref }}-${{ inputs.rerun_group }}
  cancel-in-progress: ${{ startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/heads/tideclaw/alpha/') }}
.github/workflows/full-release-validation.yml
  group: full-release-validation-${{ inputs.ref }}-${{ inputs.rerun_group }}
  cancel-in-progress: ${{ (inputs.ref == 'main' && inputs.rerun_group == 'all') || startsWith(inputs.ref, 'tideclaw/alpha/') }}
```
Observed result after fix: the real workflow YAML exposes the same concurrency values asserted by the updated tests; the focused tooling suite reports 33 passing tests.
What was not tested: no live GitHub release workflow dispatch was started; this PR only updates tests that validate checked-in workflow definitions.

